							<hr width="100%" size="1" class="hrcolor" />
							<div class="post">The problem with current gain is that its &quot;poorly characterised&quot; - which is gobbledygook for &quot;varies a lot between devices&quot;. &nbsp;So any circuit design that relies on it having a given value is a weak design. &nbsp;Typically you design for the minimum value of beta in the datasheet (note that it varies with current too...).<br /><br />Since the variation between devices can be as big a factor as 3 or 4 IIRC, this means your current limiting would also vary greatly.</div>
